plugins.author: Takamitsu Endo
plugins.name: FDN64Reverb
plugins.description: FDN64Reverb is a reverb equipped with a feedback delay network (FDN). However, the size of feedback matrix is 64.

plugins.author: Takamitsu Endo
plugins.name: EsPhaser
plugins.description: EsPhaser is a phaser with up to 4096 stages of order 2 Thiran all-pass filters. This is the same phaser used in EnvelopedSine.

plugins.author: Takamitsu Endo
plugins.name: SevenDelay
plugins.description: SevenDelay is a stereo delay with 7th order lagrange interpolated fractional delay and 7x oversampling.

plugins.author: Takamitsu Endo
plugins.name: L3Reverb
plugins.description: L4Reverb is an extended version of LatticeReverb. This time, lattice structure has 4 * 4 * 4 * 4 = 256 sections per channel.

plugins.author: Takamitsu Endo
plugins.name: WaveCymbal
plugins.description: WaveCymbal is an attempt to make a cymbal synthesizer with banded wave-guide model. The result is more like dragging bunch of empty cans or thin metal plate on asphalt rather than cymbal.

plugins.author: Takamitsu Endo
plugins.name: LatticeReverb
plugins.description: LatticeReverb is a reverb using lattice structure. Equipped with 16 delays per channel.

plugins.author: Takamitsu Endo
plugins.name: L4Reverb
plugins.description: L4Reverb is an extended version of LatticeReverb. This time, lattice structure has 4 * 4 * 4 * 4 = 256 sections per channel.

plugins.author: Takamitsu Endo
plugins.name: BasicLimiter
plugins.description: BasicLimiter is a basic single band limiter. The sound is nothing new, but the design of true peak mode is a bit luxurious.

plugins.author: Takamitsu Endo
plugins.name: BasicLimiterAutoMake
plugins.description: BasicLimiter is a basic single band limiter. The sound is nothing new, but the design of true peak mode is a bit luxurious.

plugins.author: Takamitsu Endo
plugins.name: FDNCymbal
plugins.description: FDNCymbal is a cymbal sound synthesizer. It can also be used as an effect. Unlike the name, most of metallic texture comes from Schroeder allpass section rather than FDN (feedback delay network). FDN section makes nice impact sound when `FDN.Time` is short. Tremolo is added to simulate wobbling of cymbal.

plugins.name: Wolf Spectrum
plugins.author: Wolf Plugins
plugins.description: Spectrogram plugin which supports both log and linear frequency scaling

plugins.name: Wolf Shaper
plugins.author: Wolf Plugins
plugins.description: Distortion plugin that lets you create your own waveshaping functions using a spline-based graph editor

plugins.name: Temper
plugins.author: Nick Thompson
plugins.description: Digital distortion audio plugin which builds upon traditional waveshaping techniques, using modulated filter coefficients to produce a unique phase distortion.

plugins.name: TAL-Vocoder
plugins.author: TAL Software
plugins.description: Vintage vocoder emulation with 11 bands that emulates the sound of vocoders from the early 80s

plugins.name: TAL-Reverb
plugins.author: TAL Software
plugins.description: High quality plate reverb with a vintage 80's character

plugins.name: TAL-Filter
plugins.author: TAL Software
plugins.description: Host synced filter module with different filter types, panorama and volume modulation possibilities

plugins.name: TAL-Chorus
plugins.author: TAL Software
plugins.description: Characteristics of the Juno-60 chorus.

plugins.name: Swanky Amp
plugins.author: Resonant DSP
plugins.description: Tube amplifier simulation DSP plugin which aims to capture the details in the dynamics of tube amplifiers.

plugins.name: SmartGuitarAmp
plugins.author: GuitarML
plugins.description: Uses a WaveNet model to recreate the sound of real world hardware. Models a small tube amp with a clean/lead channel. Gain and EQ knobs modulate the modeled sound.

plugins.name: Regrader
plugins.author: Igor Zinken
plugins.description: Delay effect in which the repeats degrade in various ways. Delay repeats can be synced to the host tempo and time signature and be fully automated.

plugins.name: Mverb
plugins.author: Martin Eastwood
plugins.description: Studio quality, open-source reverb. Its release was intended to provide a practical demonstration of Dattorroâ€™s figure-of-eight reverb structure and provide the open source community with a high quality reverb.

plugins.name: modEQ
plugins.author: Tobante Audio
plugins.description: EQ audio effects plugin with modulation.

plugins.name: Mini Series: 3-Band EQ
plugins.author: Filipe Coelho
plugins.description: 3-Band EQ

plugins.name: MDA
plugins.author: Paul Kellett
plugins.description: Collection of effect plug-ins, from delay to an overdrive and a vocoder.

plugins.name: IEM Plugin Suite
plugins.author: Institute of Electronic Music and Acoustics
plugins.description: Collection of ambisonic plug-ins including Compressors, Delays, Reverb, Encoders, Decoders and Visualizers

plugins.name: Dragonfly Reverb
plugins.author: Michael Willis
plugins.description: Dragonfly Reverb is a bundle of free audio effect plugins for Linux, MacOS, and Windows.

plugins.name: Diopser
plugins.author: Robbert van der Helm
plugins.description: Rotate the phase of a signal around a specific frequency without affecting its spectral content.

plugins.name: Chow Tape Model
plugins.author: Chowdhury DSP
plugins.description: Chow Tape Model is a digital emulation of a reel-to-reel analog tape machine. The original algorithm was developed to emulate the Sony TC-260, but has since been expanded to be able to model a wide variety of tape machines.

plugins.name: CHOW Matrix
plugins.author: Chowdhury DSP
plugins.description: Delay effect, made up of an infinitely growable tree of delay lines, each with individual controls for feedback, panning, distortion, and more.

plugins.name: Argotlunar
plugins.author: Michael Ourednik
plugins.description: Real-time delay-line granulator. It disintegrates an audio stream into short samples (grains). Each grain can have random settings of amplitude, panning, duration, delay, pitch, glissando, filter and envelope. The output of all grains is mixed together into a stream which can be fed back into the main input.

plugins.name: ampli-Fe
plugins.author: Anton Lazarev
plugins.description: Amplifier effect which allows the volume to be changed from 0% to 200%

plugins.name: Subhoofer
plugins.author: Ardura
plugins.description: A simple scrolling oscilloscope in rust with multichannel inputs and an analyzer

plugins.name: Scrollscope
plugins.author: Ardura
plugins.description: A simple scrolling oscilloscope in rust with multichannel inputs and an analyzer

plugins.name: Interleaf
plugins.author: Ardura
plugins.description: A simple scrolling oscilloscope in rust with multichannel inputs and an analyzer

plugins.name: Glade Desk
plugins.author: Ardura
plugins.description: Custom Console Idea

plugins.name: Airwindows
plugins.author: Chris Johnson
plugins.description: Huge collection of effects using simple UI controls.
